Don’t worry. I will do it for you.

32
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:19,160
Here you go.

33
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:24,120
You’ve been tired from work.
Do you want to take a seat?

34
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,040
Come on, come sit down.

35
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:28,960
Just sit down here,
so you can get comfortable.

36
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:30,360
Just wait a moment.

37
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:35,680
I’m coming.

38
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:37,400
Here’s some cold water.

39
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:39,760
Have a sip so you can feel fresh.

40
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:42,280
I’m not thirsty.

41
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:43,720
Even if you’re not thirsty,
you have to drink it.

42
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:44,960
You’ve been hot outside,

43
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:47,680
have a sip. You’ll be dehydrated.

44
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:51,400
Good job. I’ll give you a massage.

45
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:57,360
Here you go. Does it feel good?

46
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:02,560
What’s wrong with you today?

47
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:04,920
What’s happening?

48
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:10,640
Nothing.
I just wanted to be a good roommate.

49
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,240
What do you want? Tell me.

50
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:26,560
Well, right now I’m unemployed,

51
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:28,320
and I don’t have any cash.

52
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:32,440
So I’m going to do all the chores
instead of paying rent.

53
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:38,680
Pupaa, please, I beg you.
Don’t kick me out, please.

54
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:40,080
I really have nowhere to go.

55
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:41,720
I’ll do everything for you.

56
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:44,880
Including sweeping the floor, mopping,
washing the dishes and laundry too.

57
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:46,840
I’ll do your underwear too.

58
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,720
What did you say?

59
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:52,840
See, here. You don’t have to feel bad.

60
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:54,680
I’ve washed
my brother’s underwear before.

61
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:58,240
Don’t mess with me. Stop right there.

62
00:03:58,240 --> 00:03:59,960
No.

63
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:10,920
I won’t give it to you, unless
you promise me you won’t kick me out.

64
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:16,760
- Give it to me.
- No.

65
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:19,160
I’m not giving it to you.

66
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:41,440
You must be responsible for this.

67
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:48,420
(BOTTEGA VENETA)

68
00:04:48,420 --> 00:04:50,600
I never said
I was going to kick you out.

69
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,200
Always thinking things yourself.

70
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:56,920
Tookta made me scared.

71
00:04:58,120 --> 00:05:00,480
You’re the one who wants to go.

72
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:04,720
So you’re saying you want me to stay?

73
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,500
Anyway,

74
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:11,440
you’ve got to stay to pay for the sofa.

75
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:12,480
You can’t go anywhere yet.

76
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:20,160
So stingy.

77
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:22,320
You know I’m unemployed.

78
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:32,160
Hey you, I’m already hungry.
Do you want to go get something to eat?

79
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,720
What should we eat?

80
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:37,520
It’s so so.

81
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:38,760
How about some milk tea?

82
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:46,560
Milk tea? Sure. I’ll go buy it for you.

83
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:47,280
Okay.

84
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:48,600
You can continue shopping.

85
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:00,840
If I had the money,

86
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:02,880
I’d buy everything.

87
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:07,200
First of all, you need to get a job.

88
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,200
I know.

89
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:15,440
Is the sofa here already? So fast.

90
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:22,000
Hello, Prapai, good girl,

91
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,720
and my best friend Pupaa.

92
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:27,160
Ta, how did you get here?

93
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:30,280
Why can’t I be here?

94
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:32,280
We normally sleep
in the same room anyway.

95
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,080
This room is nice.

96
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:37,520
I’ll have a look around.

97
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:42,360
Hey.

98
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:45,640
Rule number two, no visitors.

99
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:48,400
You used to tell me Ta is an outsider.

100
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,720
Why are there rules?

101
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,720
Oh, so you guys are staying together?

102
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:09,640
I thought Prapai was just over
to hang around at your place.

103
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,600
So this is it.

104
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:16,080
What’s it about this time?

105
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,720
How did you come stay with him?

106
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:21,640
You asked her over?

107
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,920
Such a friendly person.

108
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:32,680
But living alone with a guy?

109
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,080
Ta, it’s not like that.

110
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,440
Then how is it?

111
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:39,120
Explain it to me.

112
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:44,240
I was the one who asked her to stay.

113
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:55,040
You think I believe what you just said?

114
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:57,000
Isn’t it a little too much?

115
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,600
When I asked you about Pai,

116
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,800
you never told me anything.

117
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,320
Am I still your friend?

118
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,640
If we’re going to talk now,
you’ll be full of emotions.

119
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:09,280
Let’s wait until you calm down.

120
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:12,080
I have to use my emotions.
I’m asking you for real,

121
00:08:12,080 --> 00:08:15,280
what are you thinking with Pai?

122
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:17,880
You like her, right?

123
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:20,680
So you planned to let her stay here.

124
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:22,040
And planned not to let me meet her.

125
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:24,400
How can you do this to a friend?

126
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:30,060
I told you already, didn’t I?

127
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:31,960
To keep your distance.

128
00:08:31,960 --> 00:08:33,060
Because I know,

129
00:08:33,060 --> 00:08:34,760
whoever gets close to her

130
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,560
will fall in love with her.

131
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:45,520
Darn it.

132
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,760
What does it have to be like this?

133
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:56,000
Darn it.

134
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,380
It’s like karma is after me.

135
00:09:15,380 --> 00:09:16,560
Real bad.

136
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:20,880
I’m sorry.

137
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:23,280
I was too angry.

138
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,120
Are you hurt?

139
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:28,320
Never mind.

140
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:29,880
According to Newton’s Law,

141
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,000
actions equals reactions.

142
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:33,640
So we’re equal.

143
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:45,360
If Prapai has someone caring like you,

144
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,920
I should be happy, right?

145
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:54,360
Right now, even if she just befriends
with me again,

146
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:57,560
for me,

147
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,880
it’s more than enough.

148
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:19,640
Pupaa, what did Ta do to you?

149
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,920
Why does he have to be this harsh?

150
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:25,000
Such a gangster.

151
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:27,040
Come on, let’s get you treated.

152
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,840
Someone wants to talk to you.

153
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:48,120
I don’t know either
how to make you believe what I’m saying.

154
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:56,560
That I really regret everything.

155
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:59,500
But if there is anything that I can do

156
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:00,760
to make you forgive me,

157
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:02,880
you can tell me.

158
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:05,840
I’m willing to do everything.

159
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:08,720
I just want us to be friends again.

160
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,760
I really mean everything, Pai.

161
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:20,000
You know I can’t be mad
at anyone for long.

162
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:25,800
But talking about being friends again,

163
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:28,560
I don’t think I can do it now.

164
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:34,720
It’s alright. I can wait.

165
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:38,440
Because for me,

166
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:42,120
you’re always my best friend.

167
00:11:57,200 --> 00:12:00,560
Nosy. Always on your friend’s side.

168
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:17,480
And you knew he’d punch you,
why didn’t you move?

169
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:20,040
You could’ve punched him back.

170
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:26,080
Do you think you’re the good guy
in the movies?

171
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:48,920
Why are you quiet?

172
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:50,440
Why aren’t you talking?

173
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:54,440
You make me feel...

174
00:12:58,600 --> 00:13:00,440
cold that I’m numb.

175
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,840
Do it yourself then.

176
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:37,200
Wawa.

177
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:40,720
Ta, what happened?

178
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:44,960
I’m sorry.

179
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,280
Where did you go?

180
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:49,720
Never mind. It’s not your problem.

181
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:51,880
It’s not my problem?

182
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:56,560
But I’m your girlfriend.

183
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:59,800
You left me all alone all day.

184
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:01,920
And you’re saying it’s not my problem?

185
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:05,560
Isn’t it too selfish?

186
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:09,160
Why are you like this?

187
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:13,920
Do you know you’re a bad boyfriend?

188
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:16,920
Yes, I’m a bad boyfriend.

189
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:20,040
I’m bad and why did you want to date me?

190
00:14:20,880 --> 00:14:22,720
Did I force you to like me?

191
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,120
You didn’t force me.

192
00:14:28,720 --> 00:14:31,120
I’m the only one running after you.

193
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:35,400
If I knew that
it would be this tiring and useless,

194
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:38,280
I wouldn’t have since the beginning.

195
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:22,000
Here you go. It’s still hot.

196
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:29,320
Where did you buy it from?

197
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:33,920
Don’t you think
I have any cooking skills?

198
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:39,200
Is putting it in the microwave
called having cooking skills?

199
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:45,120
You caught me.

200
00:15:58,120 --> 00:16:00,040
Is it good? Can I try?

201
00:16:01,760 --> 00:16:03,160
Go get a new spoon.

202
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:06,800
I just want to taste only a little bit.
Can I have some?

203
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:09,320
You’ll eat all the eggs if I go.
I want to eat the egg too...

204
00:16:13,560 --> 00:16:14,720
Yes, mom?

205
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:20,720
How did you know?

206
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:28,480
Ta didn’t tell you?

207
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:35,000
I should be asking you how you knew?

208
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:44,480
I already got a job,
as a Professor’s assistant.

209
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:47,440
I have to get to work now.
Talk to you later.

210
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:58,400
I’m sorry I made you hide this
from your mom.

211
00:16:59,880 --> 00:17:01,560
I’m not hiding anything.

212
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:05,480
I just don’t want my mom to bother me
during my research.

213
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:09,240
Thank you anyway.

214
00:17:10,080 --> 00:17:12,360
Then I better get to work.

215
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:18,120
Wait a minute, hold on.

216
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:20,440
What do you need?

217
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:23,320
Are you really going to go like this?

218
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,280
Wait for me.

219
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,840
What are you doing?

220
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:44,120
Taking responsible
for being the reason you got this.

221
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:46,920
Stay still or it won’t look good.

222
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:14,800
I’m going to work now.

223
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:16,680
Hold on.

224
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:21,000
I’m not even done.
Why is he in such a rush?

225
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:33,040
What are you thinking with Pai?

226
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:36,120
You like her, don’t you?

227
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:50,480
(What do I feel?)

228
00:19:03,520 --> 00:19:05,360
They say

229
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:11,040
love is more complicated than science.

230
00:19:14,640 --> 00:19:16,120
You don’t need to be shy.

231
00:19:16,840 --> 00:19:20,040
Love and teenager always come together.

232
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,760
Back when I was young,

233
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:29,440
I was everyone’s go-to person
to help out about love.

234
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:33,160
What do I have to do, Professor?

235
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:36,800
You have to prove it.

236
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:40,280
It’s not that difficult.
You can use science.

237
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:44,200
First of all, observe.

238
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:47,080
Then make an assumption,
collect all your data.

239
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:49,080
Analyze your data, and then...

240
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:50,720
Conclude.

241
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:55,960
What are you guys talking about?

242
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:58,080
Sounds like something serious.

243
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:05,680
About the scholarship, right?

244
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:10,640
There’s an opening for a
scholarship to do research.

245
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:15,240
Pupaa, if you’ve decided your
research hypothesis,

246
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:17,640
then send me the proposal.
I’ll have a look at it for you.

247
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:19,400
Yes, sir.

248
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:23,800
Meena, you’re doing your research
for your masters’ degree, right?

249
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:26,080
You can submit yours as well.

250
00:20:26,080 --> 00:20:27,960
So maybe I can submit
for the scholarship for you.

251
00:20:28,880 --> 00:20:29,880
Sure.

252
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:36,160
If you understand now,
then go try to figure it out.

253
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:38,040
Yes, sir.

254
00:20:57,720 --> 00:20:59,160
Oh Tookta.

255
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:01,280
Hello.

256
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:04,400
I have something to disturb you
for a bit.

257
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:08,600
I have a business seminar to attend
with the diamond team,

258
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:11,320
so I would like to leave Tintin with you
for a night.

259
00:21:11,320 --> 00:21:15,440
In return to the rent
I’m supposed to get.

260
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:17,240
But Pupaa said

261
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:19,720
Pai can stay without paying rent.

262
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:26,320
Sure. I’m available anyway.

263
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,080
Thank you so much.

264
00:21:28,080 --> 00:21:30,880
I’m sorry I have to bother you.

