372
00:31:38,960 --> 00:31:41,320
Our greatest scientist.

373
00:31:41,320 --> 00:31:42,920
Enjoying it like a kid, hey?

374
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:45,720
I remember when I was young,

375
00:31:45,720 --> 00:31:47,560
we were trying to catch it.

376
00:31:47,560 --> 00:31:48,440
Have you played it before?

377
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:49,640
Of course.

378
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:51,840
But my friend always beats me to it.

379
00:31:52,960 --> 00:31:55,880
But I think soon
we won’t need a book anymore.

380
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:59,680
It would be floating
right in front of us for sure.

381
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:04,960
Did you mean a hologram?

382
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:07,560
Yes, yes. I saw it in a movie before.

383
00:32:08,480 --> 00:32:12,120
If we get to see those
who we’ve lost once again,

384
00:32:12,520 --> 00:32:14,680
even though
if it’s just a virtual image,

385
00:32:15,280 --> 00:32:19,400
I think it will help a lot for those
who are longing.

386
00:32:28,400 --> 00:32:30,080
I got an idea for my research topic.

387
00:32:31,040 --> 00:32:34,040
I will develop hologram
to become more realistic.

388
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:37,240
Maybe by including more
computer technologies.

389
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:39,160
It should be a great research topic.

390
00:32:40,480 --> 00:32:41,720
Thanks to you.

391
00:32:51,720 --> 00:32:53,640
I think we should head back.

392
00:32:53,640 --> 00:32:55,880
Tookta should be coming
to pick up Tintin soon.

393
00:32:59,120 --> 00:33:00,480
Where’s Tintin?

394
00:33:05,320 --> 00:33:06,320
Should we split up?

395
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:10,640
Tintin, Tintin.

396
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:16,600
Mom, mom.

397
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:20,760
Oh, this isn’t mom.

398
00:33:21,200 --> 00:33:24,440
Where are mom and dad?

399
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:26,360
It’s alright. Don’t cry.

400
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:33,800
Tintin, are you alright?

401
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:36,520
Why did you go wandering around?
I was worried.

402
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:39,440
I’m sorry, dad.

403
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:41,240
Is this your child?

404
00:33:46,640 --> 00:33:47,800
No.

405
00:33:49,880 --> 00:33:53,080
Dad, where’s mom?

406
00:33:53,080 --> 00:33:54,440
Tintin, Tintin.

407
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:58,360
Where did you go? I was worried sick.

408
00:33:58,880 --> 00:34:00,200
Are you alright?

409
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:01,960
Are both of you

410
00:34:03,360 --> 00:34:05,240
taking your kid out for a walk?

411
00:34:07,360 --> 00:34:09,240
No. No, we’re not.

412
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:13,620
Mom and dad, I want to go home now.

413
00:34:13,620 --> 00:34:16,000
Let’s go home.

414
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:19,320
Okay, let’s go home.

415
00:34:20,680 --> 00:34:22,680
I’ll have to excuse myself.

416
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:28,320
Me too.

417
00:34:29,080 --> 00:34:30,040
Wait for me.

418
00:34:33,140 --> 00:34:38,180
(BOTTEGA VENETA)

419
00:34:53,760 --> 00:34:55,880
About your senior colleague.

420
00:34:56,280 --> 00:34:59,080
I think she’ll misunderstand.

421
00:34:59,880 --> 00:35:01,440
We just ran out like this.

422
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:04,560
You should explain to her.

423
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:06,800
Otherwise, I’ll be the one to blame.

424
00:35:08,520 --> 00:35:09,440
Um.

425
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:17,960
Even if it was a bit hectic today,

426
00:35:17,960 --> 00:35:19,440
but it was a good day, right?

427
00:35:22,880 --> 00:35:24,480
What’s the difference
between these two images?

428
00:35:24,940 --> 00:35:26,660
Cheese and...

429
00:35:26,660 --> 00:35:28,900
Cheese? You know cheese?

430
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:31,480
I’ll get it.

431
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:35,000
What else is there?

432
00:35:37,060 --> 00:35:37,860
Eyes.

433
00:35:38,140 --> 00:35:38,700
Eyes.

